    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-04-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-04-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="77"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d77">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 5301/2.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Wilson</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-04-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 3, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 97.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    dispatch, No. 157, of the 7th ultimo, referring to the complaint of a company
                    dealing <pb facs="0191" n="79" xml:id="pg_79"/> in American lubricating oils
                    that the Belgian Government discriminated against such products by inserting in
                    the specifications of supply bids for furnishing oils to the government railways
                    the requirement of “Russian” origin.</p>
                <p>Your correspondence with the Belgian Government, resulting in its removal of the
                    discrimination, copies of which accompany your dispatch, have been read with
                    interest; and the department desires to commend your action and to express
                    gratification at the success of your representations.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Bacon.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
